Background:

The world is becoming more urbanized. This is overall a really good thing; it is more environmentally friendly, better for the economy, and enables people to exchange ideas and inspiration. One downside of the city, however, is the tight spaces those who live there are squeezed into. In the Fall of 2018, Stanley Black and Decker commissioned the design of a kitchen product to break into the global market. Through over 90 user interviews and 70 survey responses from people living in Asian Pacific cities, we learned that 80% people are frustrated with their small kitchen space and were willing to pay for a solution.
